---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="MUN Quant Society"
  subtitle="Director, Data & Infrastructure · Sep 2025 – Present · 11 Contributors"
  logo="/logos/mqs.png"
  logoAlt="MUN Quant Society"
  context="Team"
  tags={["Python", "PostgreSQL", "PyTorch", "FinBERT", "GCP", "GitHub Actions", "FMP API", "pandas", "NumPy"]}
>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-600 text-white/80 mb-4">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-4">
      As Director of Data & Infrastructure, I lead a team of 11 contributors building the 
      society's end-to-end quantitative trading platform. The system supports multi-portfolio 
      live trading with concurrent execution, an event-driven backtesting engine, a real-time 
      NLP sentiment pipeline, and a full risk management layer — all backed by PostgreSQL 
      and deployed on GCP.
    </p>
    <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
      The codebase spans approximately 1,600 lines across core infrastructure, with 
      extensive workflow documentation, a pytest test suite, and CI/CD via GitHub Actions. 
      It is open source and actively maintained.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/MUNQuantSociety/MQSMaster" target="_blank" class="detail-link mt-3 inline-block">View on GitHub →</a>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-600 text-white/80 mb-6">System Architecture</h2>
    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Live Trading Engine -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">Live Trading Engine</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">src/live_trading/ · Concurrent multi-portfolio execution</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The live trading engine runs each portfolio strategy in its own thread with a 
          configurable poll interval. Each cycle fetches an atomic portfolio state snapshot 
          from the database (cash, positions, market data), updates technical indicators, 
          builds a StrategyContext, and calls the strategy's OnData method to generate 
          trade signals. A circuit breaker pattern halts individual portfolio threads after 
          consecutive failures to prevent cascading issues across strategies.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          <span class="tech-tag">Threading</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Circuit Breaker</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Connection Pooling</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">FMP API</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Backtesting Framework -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">Backtesting Framework</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">src/backtest/ · Event-driven + vectorized backtesting</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The backtesting engine supports both event-driven and vectorized modes. The 
          event-driven BacktestRunner simulates an event loop — grouping historical data by 
          timestamp, applying configurable slippage, and running each strategy's signal 
          generation with a sliding lookback window. The BacktestExecutor simulates trade 
          execution with a full margin model supporting long/short positions and configurable 
          leverage. Generates comprehensive reports: trade logs, performance timeseries, 
          Sharpe ratio, max drawdown, rolling statistics (30D/90D/180D), monthly returns, 
          and benchmark comparisons against buy-and-hold.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          <span class="tech-tag">Event-Driven Simulation</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Vectorized Backtesting</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Margin Model</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Sharpe / Drawdown</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Strategy API & Indicators -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">Strategy API & Indicator System</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">src/portfolios/ · 4 live strategies, 7 built-in indicators</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Strategies inherit from a BasePortfolio abstract class that provides a clean 
          StrategyContext API with MarketData access (OHLCV, history, existence checks), 
          PortfolioManager (cash, positions, weights), and buy/sell methods with confidence-weighted 
          position sizing. The indicator system uses a dynamic factory (importlib) with 
          automatic warmup from historical data. Built-in indicators include SMA, RSI, RMI, 
          ATR, Displaced Moving Average, Rate of Change, and VWAP. Four active strategies: 
          VolMomentum, MomentumStrategy, RegimeAdaptiveStrategy, and TrendRotateStrategy.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          <span class="tech-tag">Abstract Base Pattern</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Dynamic Factory</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">SMA / RSI / ATR / VWAP</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Confidence Sizing</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- NLP Pipeline -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">NLP Sentiment Analysis Pipeline</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">NLP/ · FinBERT · Multi-source scraping · 5-minute daemon</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A daemon-based pipeline that scrapes financial news from multiple sources (FMP, 
          Yahoo Finance, Finviz, Alpha Vantage) every 5 minutes in batched ticker groups to 
          avoid rate limiting. Articles are deduplicated, merged into per-ticker CSVs, and 
          processed through a FinBERT transformer model for sentiment scoring (-1.0 to 1.0). 
          Results are stored in a PostgreSQL news_sentiment table for real-time access by 
          trading strategies. Includes visualization notebooks for sentiment trend analysis.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          <span class="tech-tag">FinBERT</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">PyTorch</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Transformers</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Web Scraping</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Daemon Process</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Data Layer -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">Data Pipeline & Database Layer</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">src/common/database/ · src/orchestrator/ · PostgreSQL</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The data layer centers on a thread-safe MQSDBConnector with a PostgreSQL connection 
          pool (minconn=1, maxconn=6). The FMPMarketData client implements rate limiting 
          (3,000 req/min with sliding window), retry logic (6 attempts), and timeout handling. 
          The backfill service generates business day ranges, batches API calls, caches to CSV, 
          and bulk-inserts with conflict handling. The schema includes five core tables: 
          market_data, cash_equity_book, positions_book, trade_execution_logs, and pnl_book — 
          with atomic state queries using CTEs for consistent portfolio snapshots.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          <span class="tech-tag">PostgreSQL</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Connection Pool</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Rate Limiting</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Bulk Insert</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">CTE Queries</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Risk Management -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">Risk Management & Capital Allocation</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">src/risk_manager/ · Daily rebalancing · Master portfolio model</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Capital flows through a master portfolio (ID: 0) that distributes to strategy 
          portfolios via weighted daily rebalancing. The DailyAllocator calculates each 
          strategy's total value (cash + marked-to-market positions), computes target 
          allocations, and executes internal transfers as paired trade_execution_log entries. 
          Supports external capital add/withdraw operations with balance validation. All 
          transfers are atomic database transactions.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          <span class="tech-tag">Daily Rebalancing</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Weighted Allocation</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Atomic Transactions</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">CLI Tools</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- OMS Design -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">Order Management System (In Progress)</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">docs/OMS_DESIGN.md · VWAP / TWAP algorithms</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
          Designing an OMS layer between strategy intent and market execution. Replaces the 
          current fire-and-forget model with parent/child order lifecycles, VWAP and TWAP 
          execution algorithms for slicing large orders over time, an AlgoScheduler for 
          timed child order dispatch, and an OrderTracker for full lifecycle visibility 
          (pending, partially filled, complete, cancelled).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CI/CD & Testing -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-600 text-white/85 mb-2">CI/CD & Testing</h3>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-white/25 mb-3">.github/workflows/ · tests/ · pytest</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
          GitHub Actions workflows for automated testing on push. The test suite covers 
          backtest engine execution, strategy API endpoints, trade execution, vectorized 
          backtesting, and indicator correctness (e.g. Relative Momentum Index). 
          Configuration-driven test fixtures with conftest.py for database mocking.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>